    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="803"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/762: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 24, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>359. Shanghai’s 1350, October 19, 6 p.m., in regard to Chinese Customs, which has
                    been forwarded to you by mail. It is suggested that, bearing in mind our
                    position as set forth during the past year in telegraphic instructions to your
                    office, you avail yourself of a convenient opportunity to discuss this matter
                    with your British and French colleagues and that you inform the Department of
                    the result of your discussions and of your views in the matter.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
